ctional-typological terms does not require reading fluency in Latin, since all examples are translated into English  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aLatin languagexSyntax. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh  aHistorical Linguistics.  aLatin/ Language.  aSyntax.1 aBaldi, Philip, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBaldi, Philip, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aCuzzolin, Pierluigi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHaverling, Gerd V. M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLuraghi, Silvia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMagni, Elisabetta, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRicca, Davide, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1z978311023857008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Linguistics and Semiotics  2000-2014 (EN)z978311023845708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Linguistics and Semiotics 2000 - 2014z9783110636970oZDB-23-DLS08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDe Gruyter Mouton Backlist 2000-2015z978311074296108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2010z9783110233544oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PACKAGE ENGLISH LANGUAGES TITLES 2010z978311023355108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PACKAGE ENGLISH LINGUISTICS 2010z978311023356808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET LINGUISTIK UND LITERATURWISSENSCHAFT  2010z9783110233605oZDB-23-DGA0 cpri